    • Method Detail

      • getRangeSize

        public double getRangeSize()
        Get the range size. If the range is [0,10] then the range is 10.0. If the range is [.5,1.5], the range is 1.0, etc. Useful for normalizing. Behavior is undefined if min or max has a special value.
        Returns:
        The size of the range (max-min) if neither is a special value (NEGINF, UNSPEC, etc)
